pullRequest.body:
Given a commutative semiring `R`, an `R`-bialgebra (resp. `R`-Hopf algebra) `A`, and a(n) (additive) monoid (resp. (additive) group) `G`, this PR defines the `R`-bialgebra (resp. `R`-Hopf algebra) structure on `(Add)MonoidAlgebra A G`. 

---

I've added a little API for monoid algebras that duplicates API for `Finsupp`, because I needed to go back and forth between using monoid algebra facts and `Finsupp` facts in proofs, and this seemed to be the cleanest way to do that.

In case you are wondering, CI fails due to an (expected) issue that is fixed in #13608.  I will merge that PR as soon as it is green.

The underlying reason is that the failing step inspects the PR and a version of master.  When writing the PR, the version of master used did not have the new scripts, so they had to be pulled in.  Now, the branch from which they were pulled is no longer accessible, but master has the files.
I see, thank you very much!
The PR causing the issue has been merged: if you merge master again, this will be a good test for whether the issue is resolved!  :smile:

@101damnations Coming here for PR triage: thanks for your PR. Can you fix the merge conflict, please? That makes it more likely to get reviewed, and it would be a shame for this PR to silently wither away.

Thank you! As well as mentioning G_m I've added the actual Hopf algebra instance on Laurent polynomials + some API. (And also, my bad, I forgot G_a works a bit differently, so this PR doesn't cover that. But I've nearly finished the corresponding Hopf algebra instance on polynomials, so I'll open a PR for that next.)
ðŸš€ Pull request has been placed on the maintainer queue by kbuzzard.

Thanks!

maintainer merge

This looks great to me, it looks like very uncontroversial additions. Maybe you could mention somewhere what the point of these results is? My understanding is that you're making G_a and G_m into R-group-schemes (and possibly other things too?) but you never mention this.

Thanks!

maintainer merge
This is apparently not needed!
For this first result (and possibly the next few) I bet you don't need A to be a bialgebra.
Again presumably you don't need A to be a bialgebra until a bit later.
Presumably this is unnecessary?
(and this)
This lemma breaks the MonoidAlgebra / Finsupp abstraction, so probably shouldn't exist

I needed to use linearity of `single`, and then, afterwards, properties of the multiplication on `A[G]` in e.g. `MonoidAlgebra.instBialgebra`. And if I use `Finsupp.lsingle, Finsupp.lhom_ext` then the monoid algebra gets unfolded to `Finsupp` too early; adding `MonoidAlgebra.lsingle` was the best way I could think of to get around this
The `@[ext]` lemma should be the one about composition with `lsingle`
See https://leanprover-community.github.io/mathlib4_docs/Mathlib/Algebra/Polynomial/Basic.html#Polynomial.lhom_ext%27 for an example.

nit
```suggestion
instance instBialgebra : Bialgebra R (MonoidAlgebra A X) where
  __ := instCoalgebra R A X
```
and reduce the indents below

This definition is arguably a bad idea, because now you have separate `HopfAlgebra.antipode` and `MonoidAlgebra.algebra` definitions, and lemmas have to pick which spelling to use.

Some options here:
* Make it clear in the docstring that `HopfAlgebra.antipode` is the preferred spelling
* Add a `simp` lemma turning this spelling into `HopfAlgebra.antipode`
* Pull out a `HopfAlgebraStruct` base class from `HopfAlgebra` that contains just the antipode (and perhaps bialgebra structure), so that you can create this data first before proving `antipode_single`.
Thanks for the review! I like the third option so I've gone with that.

nit:
```suggestion
end AddMonoidAlgebra

namespace LaurentPolynomial
```
I think you can drop this line?
Don't these theorems belong in the file about Coalgebras? I think they only need `Coalgebra R A`).
Thanks, done - I've moved the API for the coalgebra structure on monoid algebras to the coalgebra file too.
Just to re-iterate; this lemma is bad, as it unfolds across the API boundary. Given it seems you don't use it anyway, can you just delete it? (same for the `AddMonoidAlgebra` version).
Gahh I'm sorry, I misread the original comment as being about the whole `lsingle` section which is why I was confused. I've removed the lemma(s) now.
To be super clear, the new `lsingle` definition is a good idea ðŸ™‚.
This should be stated with function composition, per "partially-applied ext lemmas". I  believe the proof is then `Finsupp.lhom_ext'`
